				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {E_{\text{tot}}} = E\left( {{\text{closed}}\;{\text{conformation}}} \right) - E\left( {\text{openconformation}} \right) $$\end{document}where Etot indicates the total energy of the intramolecular hydrogen bond, whereas E(closed conformation) and E(open conformation) are the energies obtained after the geometry optimization procedures for closed and open conformations.

Two homodesmotic reaction schemes presented in Schemes 4 or 5 allow us to estimate the overall energy associated with intramolecular H-bond formation:
2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {E_{\text{tot}}} = {\text{SESE}}\left( {\text{II}} \right) - {\text{SESE}}\left( {\text{I}} \right) $$\end{document}

Following Grabowski’s method [43, 45], the “pure” energy of H-bonding, EHB, can be obtained as:
3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {E_{\text{HB}}} = E\left( {{\text{open conformation}}\_{\text{O}} - {\text{H rotated 18}}0^\circ } \right)--E\left( {{\text{open conformation}},\;{\text{optimized}}} \right) $$\end{document}where E(open conformation_O-H rotated 180°) means the energy of the single point calculation for the closed conformer formed from that obtained from the open one after the rotation of O–H around the C–O single bond. The difference between the total and above energies is the energy due to the changes in geometry, sometimes called the energy of delocalization, Edeloc:
4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {E_{\text{deloc}}} = {E_{\text{tot}}} - {E_{\text{HB}}} $$\end{document}
